                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Terrible Uses for Micro SD Cards]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/terrible-uses-for-micro-sd-cards/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/illustration_of_microsd_cards_and_a_sim_tray_with_red_x_symbols_over_them.png" length="2567" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[storage]]></category><category><![CDATA[SSD]]></category><category><![CDATA[Backup & Recovery]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Convenient? Yes. Trustworthy? Not on your life!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>SD and Micro SD cards are wonderful little storage devices, and sometimes I can't believe that I'm holding hundreds of gigabytes in the palm of my hand in something the size of my pinkie nail.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 12:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/terrible-uses-for-micro-sd-cards/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Frame Generation Is Becoming Mandatory in Some PC Games, and I Don’t Like It]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/frame-generation-mandatory-in-pc-games-i-dont-like-it/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Goran Damnjanovic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/geforce-rtx-5090.jpg" length="1979" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Nvidia]]></category><category><![CDATA[AMD]]></category><category><![CDATA[Monster Hunter Wilds]]></category><category><![CDATA[Borderlands 4]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            60FPS, but only with frame generation. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>You may have noticed that some PC games now list frame generation as part of their system requirements. The issue here is that system requirements for PC games usually target 60 FPS performance, and playing games at 60 FPS with frame generation feels anything but good.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 12:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/frame-generation-mandatory-in-pc-games-i-dont-like-it/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft's Local Accounts Crackdown Is Yet Another Reason to Install Linux]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/microsofts-local-accounts-crackdown-is-yet-another-reason-to-install-linux/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jordan Gloor]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/tux-the-linux-penguin-peeking-from-behind-a-windows-11-user-icon-above-a-local-account-button-with-red-error-and-cross-symbols.png" length="959" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[Open Source]]></category><category><![CDATA[Kubuntu Focus M2 Gen 6]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Will this be the final straw for you?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you're like me, you've been relying on technical workarounds to set up Windows 11 with a local account instead of the required Microsoft account. Unfortunately, <a href="https://www.xda-developers.com/microsoft-cracking-down-people-creating-local-accounts-windows/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Microsoft is shutting down more of those workarounds</a>, which is just affirming my decision to replace Windows with Linux as my daily driver desktop.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 11:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/microsofts-local-accounts-crackdown-is-yet-another-reason-to-install-linux/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why I Still Use a 5-Year-Old Mac Mini in 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-i-still-use-a-5-year-old-mac-mini-in-2025/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/pic-3.jpg" length="775" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Mac mini (M2, 2023)]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mini PC]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[macOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Home Assistant]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            No signs of stopping.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I have no plans to replace the five-year-old Mac mini that’s gracefully aging beneath my TV. I’ll happily buy another when the time comes, but that day still feels like a long way off.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 11:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-i-still-use-a-5-year-old-mac-mini-in-2025/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[These Aren't My Favorite Earbuds, but They're the Ones I'd Buy]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/jlab-go-pods-anc-review/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bertel King]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/10/p1050011-1-1.jpg" length="2930" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[JLab GO Pods ANC]]></category><category><![CDATA[JLab]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Unfortunately, the worst part about them is included in the name.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>At half the price of their more premium counterparts yet almost indistinguishable in both looks and sound, the <a href="https://www.jlab.com/products/go-pods-anc-true-wireless-earbuds-black" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" target="_blank">JLab GO Pods ANC</a> are budget earbuds done right. Plus, at such a small size, the price is hardly the only reason to buy.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Thu, 09 Oct 2025 10:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/jlab-go-pods-anc-review/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why Sega’s $70 Million Flop Is the Best Game of All Time]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-segas-70-million-flop-is-the-best-game-of-all-time/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/playing-hang-on-in-shenmue.jpg" length="2540" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Shenmue]]></category><category><![CDATA[Shenmue 2]]></category><category><![CDATA[Retro Gaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            How to revolutionize gaming and burn a load of cash at the same time.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>In late 1999, after spending $70 million developing what was then the most expensive game ever made, SEGA released <em>Shenmue</em> for the Dreamcast. Though the world was a better place for it, the game did not recover its development costs, nor did it get the audience it deserved.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 22:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-segas-70-million-flop-is-the-best-game-of-all-time/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Features That Would Take Every Browser to the Next Level]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/features-that-would-take-web-browsers-to-the-next-level/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Graeme Peacock]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/smiling-man-sitting-cross-legged-with-a-laptop-surrounded-by-code-snippets-web-browser-graphics-and-internet-icons-on-a-bright-blue-background.png" length="1318" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Web]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Chrome]]></category><category><![CDATA[Firefox]]></category><category><![CDATA[web browsers]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            We don’t browse aimlessly; we browse with purpose. So why don’t browsers support that?  
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Do you ever get excited about new browser releases anymore? Have you noticed how they all look the same these days? There's nothing unique about any of them; they don't innovate, and that's boring. I have 5 features that would take web browsers to the next level.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 21:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/features-that-would-take-web-browsers-to-the-next-level/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Alien: Earth’s End-Credit Music Shreds Harder Than a Xenomorph]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/alien-earths-end-credit-music-explained/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Derek Malcolm]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/xenomorph-from-alien-earth-standing-between-james-hetfield-and-josh-homme-surrounded-by-smoke-and-dramatic-stage-lighting.png" length="2546" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Alien: Earth]]></category><category><![CDATA[TV Shows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Disney+]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hulu]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Aliens, cyborgs, and some of the hardest rock and metal songs of the '80s, '90s, and 2000s. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><a href="https://disneyplus.bn5x.net/c/156932/564546/9358?subId1=UUhtgUeUpU2017171&subId2=ehtg&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.disneyplus.com%2Fbrowse%2Fentity-23c8484e-a657-440b-8bf9-678f547331ff" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim"><em>Alien Earth</em></a> has so far been one of my favorite new series of the year. For the uninitiated, it's the critically acclaimed FX sci-fi thriller series streaming on Disney+ and Hulu that, for fans of the Alien universe of films, situates itself in the timeline between the later prequel films and 1979's original <em>Alien</em>.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 20:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/alien-earths-end-credit-music-explained/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Used Luxury Crossover Now Costs Less Than a New Honda Civic]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/used-luxury-crossover-costs-less-than-new-honda-civic/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tyler Dupont]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/lexus_ux_250h_cadmium_orange_003_81c5060262beafe7101eb675b0cd83b038014498.jpg" length="1045" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Lexus]]></category><category><![CDATA[Luxury Cars]]></category><category><![CDATA[SUVs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Honda]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A used luxury crossover now offers premium comfort and value for less than a brand-new Civic.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Luxury cars have a reputation for steep prices, but some used models are changing that perception. One used luxury crossover, in particular, now undercuts the cost of a brand-new Honda Civic, and it offers far more refinement for the money.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 19:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/used-luxury-crossover-costs-less-than-new-honda-civic/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Ninite Is the Best Way to Bulk Install Windows Programs on A New PC]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/ninite-is-the-best-way-to-bulk-install-windows-programs-on-a-new-pc/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/windows-11-logo-with-several-apps-around-it.jpg" length="798" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Discord]]></category><category><![CDATA[Steam]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Never use Edge to download Chrome again.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Are you tired of having to navigate to a dozen different download pages after getting a new computer, just to get the software you want to use installed? If so, Ninite is the answer to your problems.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Wed, 08 Oct 2025 19:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/ninite-is-the-best-way-to-bulk-install-windows-programs-on-a-new-pc/</guid></item></channel>
